<title type="html"><![CDATA[Ahl al-Hadith - Salafiyyah &amp; What Opposes It • Emphasis on following the Salaf as opposed to following the Khalaf]]></title>

<category term="Ahl al-Hadith - Salafiyyah &amp; What Opposes It" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=40" label="Ahl al-Hadith - Salafiyyah &amp; What Opposes It"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1573&amp;p=1693#p1693"><![CDATA[
<strong>Emphasis on following the Salaf as opposed to following the Khalaf</strong><br /><br />The Thiqah Imām ʿAbullāh Bin Dawūd al-Khārībī (Died 213 Hijrī) said, <br /><br /><strong>&quot;I swear by Allah! If it reached us that the righteous Salaf only washed their nails in wudhu then we would not do more than this.&quot; </strong><br /><br /><em>(Al-Faqīh wal-Mutafiqh no.403 and its chain is Sahīh)</em><br /><br />Imām Ibn Khuzaīmah (Died 311 Hijrī) said, <br /><br /><strong>&quot;The meaning (of the above saying of the Imām) is that the religion is to follow (the righteous Salaf).&quot; </strong><br /><br /><em>(Al-Faqīh wal-Mutafiqh no.403 and its chain is Sahīh)<br /><br />Translated by Abu Ubaydah</em><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">Abu Ubaydah</a> — Thu Apr 23, 2020 3:19 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
