<category term="Ahl al-Hadith - Salafiyyah &amp; What Opposes It" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=40" label="Ahl al-Hadith - Salafiyyah &amp; What Opposes It"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1543&amp;p=1659#p1659"><![CDATA[
FAWA'ID SHAYKH UBAYDULLAH MUBARAKPURI (d.1414) - 2 -<br /><br />Shaykh Muhammad Yunus Madanī of India of Banaras narrated to me in 1998, that once a group of Scholars of India and one Arab Scholar visited Shaykh al-Hadīth Ubaydullāh Mubārakpūrī and they asked him who is biggest scholar in the world today? Shaykh Ubaydullāh attempted to avoid the question but upon repeated requests, the Shaykh replied and said, <br /><br />Shaykh ‘Ata Allāh Hanīf Bhojiyānī<br />Shaykh ‘Abd al-Azīz bin ‘Abd Allāh bin Bāz<br />Shaykh Muhammad Nasir al-Dīn al-Albānī<br /><br />So yet again, we see the people of knowledge, specialists scholars of Hadith and Aqidah, Imams of Manhaj and the fiqh of Ahl al-Sunnah wa Ahl al-Hadith are recognised by other scholars of equal calibre. May Allah forgive them and have mercy on them Rahimahumullah. Amin<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=48">AbuKhuzaimahAnsari</a> — Tue Apr 10, 2018 10:25 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
